trans-unit.source: Running the NsSample sample program
To run the <codeph>NsSample</codeph> program, follow these steps.

trans-unit.source: Open a command prompt and change to the <codeph>%<ph conref="../conrefs.dita#prod/productinstallpath"></ph>%\demo\</codeph> directory, where <codeph>%<ph conref="../conrefs.dita#prod/productinstallpath"></ph>%</codeph> is the directory where you installed <ph conref="../conrefs.dita#prod/productshortname"></ph>.

trans-unit.source: Set the CLASSPATH to the current directory ("."), and also include the following jar files in order to use the Network Server and the network client driver:

trans-unit.source: <codeph>derbynet.jar</codeph>
The Network Server jar file. It must be in your CLASSPATH to use any of the Network Server functions.

seg-source.mrk: It must be in your CLASSPATH to use any of the Network Server functions.

target.mrk: It must be in your CLASSPATH to use any of the Network Server functions.

trans-unit.source: <codeph>derbyclient.jar</codeph>
This jar file must be in your CLASSPATH to use the Network Client driver.

target.mrk: This jar file must be in your CLASSPATH to use the Network Client driver.

trans-unit.source: <codeph>derby.jar</codeph>
The <ph conref="../conrefs.dita#prod/productshortname"></ph> database engine jar file.
<codeph>derbytools.jar</codeph>
The <ph conref="../conrefs.dita#prod/productshortname"></ph> tools jar file.
Test the CLASSPATH settings by running the following Java command:

trans-unit.source: java org.apache.derby.tools.sysinfo
This command shows the <ph conref="../conrefs.dita#prod/productshortname"></ph> jar files that are in the classpath as well as their respective versions.
